01:57:20.080 --> 01:57:22.291
At least he's a fair man.

01:57:22.791 --> 01:57:24.585
I'll let it sit with him.

01:57:39.686 --> 01:57:41.062
PATTON:
George...

01:57:42.315 --> 01:57:44.609
...our war is over.

01:57:44.817 --> 01:57:46.068
Over, sir?

01:57:46.653 --> 01:57:50.034
Is just a question of waiting
for the orders now.

01:57:57.583 --> 01:57:59.418
I feel I'm...

01:58:01.086 --> 01:58:05.466
I'm destined to achieve some
great thing. What, I don't know.

01:58:07.218 --> 01:58:11.306
But this last incident is...

01:58:12.098 --> 01:58:16.104
...so trivial in its nature
and so terrible in its effect-

01:58:16.687 --> 01:58:20.275
It can't be an accident.
It has to be the work of God.

01:58:21.193 --> 01:58:22.567
Yes, sir.

01:58:23.236 --> 01:58:25.779
The last great opportunity
of a lifetime...

01:58:25.989 --> 01:58:30.492
...an entire world at war
and I'm left out of it?

01:58:30.745 --> 01:58:32.121
No, sir.

01:58:32.330 --> 01:58:34.415
God will not permit this to happen!

01:58:34.873 --> 01:58:39.464
I am going to be allowed
to fulfil my destiny!

01:58:44.426 --> 01:58:46.345
His will be done.

01:58:58.945 --> 01:59:02.489
NARRATOR: In the greatest amphibious
operation ever attempted...

01:59:02.696 --> 01:59:05.408
...a predawn naval bombardment
prepares the way...

01:59:05.618 --> 01:59:08.663
...for allied soldiers to assault
the Normandy beaches...

01:59:08.872 --> 01:59:12.460
...and claw out a desperate foothold
on the continent of Europe.

01:59:27.602 --> 01:59:32.858
I knew Montgomery couldn't take Caen
on D-day or D-plus-10. And I said so.

01:59:33.105 --> 01:59:37.030
And here they are all hung up
in the hedgerow country.

01:59:37.322 --> 01:59:41.409
They should pivot the way von
Schlieffen planned it in World War I.

01:59:42.325 --> 01:59:45.996
Then we might get a chance to do
some real broken field running.

01:59:46.997 --> 01:59:48.917
But they don't listen to me.

01:59:52.089 --> 01:59:54.590
What a way to enter
the continent of Europe.

01:59:54.839 --> 01:59:57.261
Along with all the rest
of the spare parts.

01:59:57.885 --> 02:00:00.595
Sir, everything on this plane
is high priority.

02:00:01.724 --> 02:00:05.520
Gen. Bradley wouldn't send for you
unless he had something in mind.

02:00:05.727 --> 02:00:09.357
I'll tell you, Cod.
I've learned my lesson.

02:00:09.983 --> 02:00:13.529
If I ever do get another chance,
I'm gonna keep my mouth shut.

02:00:15.364 --> 02:00:17.282
I'm gonna play the game.

02:00:17.743 --> 02:00:19.787
If I forget, you remind me.

02:00:20.535 --> 02:00:24.916
- I'll give a gentle nudge in the ribs.
- Give me a swift kick in the ass.

02:00:25.707 --> 02:00:27.001
Yes, sir.

02:00:48.819 --> 02:00:50.363
Welcome to France, sir.

02:00:50.570 --> 02:00:53.033
Hope the war's still on.
Where's the boss?

02:00:53.240 --> 02:00:54.491
Right this way, sir.

02:01:31.701 --> 02:01:35.289
Patton, haven't seen you
since Messina.

02:01:35.496 --> 02:01:36.539
How are you?

02:01:36.747 --> 02:01:39.502
You're doing a splendid job
decoying the Jerries.

02:01:39.709 --> 02:01:42.254
You'll forgive me,
I'm off to the front.

02:01:42.464 --> 02:01:44.257
Best of everything, old boy.

02:01:48.387 --> 02:01:49.889
By the way...

02:01:50.348 --> 02:01:53.809
...intelligence confirms
that I'm against Rommel again.

02:01:58.522 --> 02:01:59.900
Rommel.

02:02:01.860 --> 02:02:03.321
Hi, how are you, George?

02:02:04.236 --> 02:02:07.617
